HEADWORD: Boanerges
<hw>Bo`a*ner"ges</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[Gr. <ets><?/</ets>, fr.
Heb. <ets>bn⟦emac⟧ hargem</ets> sons of thunder. -- an appellation given
by Christ to two of his disciples (James and John). See <ets>Mark</ets>
iii. 17.]</ety> <def>Any declamatory and vociferous preacher or
orator.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

